commit.message: Update to Unicode 15.1.0
Update copyright year to 2024

Update Autoconf macros

Notes from running autoupdate:
The preprocessor macro `STDC_HEADERS' is obsolete.
  Except in unusual embedded environments, you can safely include all
  ISO C90 headers unconditionally.
AC_CHECK_INCLUDES_DEFAULT
AC_PROG_EGREP
Increase version to 2.5.12
Upgrade zlib to 1.2.13
Update copyright year to 2023

Update to Unicode 15.0.0

The update script was changed to use curl instead of wget.
The wget command was being run with the timestamp option (-N)
which would fail if the local repo had been created after
the files had been updated at unicode.org (therefore having a newer
timestamp). Turning off the timestamp option would cause wget
to create a file with a numeric suffix (NormalizationTest.txt.1)
which would not be read for running tests.
Update copyright year to 2022
Fixed small typo + dropped extension as it's already added automatically.
Dropped the attempt at short sha.
Tried again with the syntax error.
Dropped the attempt at shortening the sha.
Shortened sha and hard-code platform for Windows.
Dropped release tag variable for now, fix multiline run.
Added missed names to the extra runs, removed stray line.
Added packaging step (dmg building) to macOS, named artifacts
Removed deprecate step (since 10.15 Catalina).
Maps should be ASCII or UTF-8
Documentation was also updated
Increase version to 2.5.11
Forgot to change some URLs

Update to Unicode 14.0.0

Also update GitHub Actions to produce an artifact for download.

Update documentation, especially URLs

One of the documentation changes was what version of Ubuntu
the Windows binaries are built on, this change was also made
in the GitHub Actions configuration.
Update copyright year to 2021
Make the status badges link to the workflow pages
